{"title_page": "Central Bank of Seychelles", "text_new": "{{short description|Central bank  Seychelles}}\n{{Infobox central bank\n| bank_name            = Central Bank of Seychelles\n| bank_name_in_local   = Banque centrale des Seychelles <br />Labank santral Sesel\n| image_1              = Central Bank of Seychelles.jpg\n| image_title_1 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0  = The main office building of Central Bank of Seychelles\n| image_width_1        = \n| image_2              =\n| image_title_2        =\n| image_width_2        =\n| headquarters         = [[Victoria, Seychelles]]\n| coordinates          = {{coord|04|37|24|S|55|27|14|E|display=inline,title}}\n| established          = {{start date and years ago| 1983|01|01|df=y}}\n| ownership            = [[Government of Seychelles]]\n| president            = [[Caroline Abel]]\n| leader_title         = Governor\n| bank_of              = [[Seychelles]]\n| currency             = [[Seychellois rupee]]\n| currency_iso         = SCR\n| logo                 = CENTRAL BANK OF SEYCHELLES LOGO.png\n| reserves             =\n| reserve_requirements = \n| borrowing_rate       = \n| interest_rate_target = \n| deposit_rate         = \n| IOER                 = \n| website              = {{URL|www.cbs.sc}}\n| preceded             =\n| succeeded            =\n| footnotes            =\n}}\n\nThe '''Central Bank of Seychelles''' ({{lang-fr|Banque centrale des Seychelles}}, [[Seychellois Creole]]: ''Labank santral Sesel''), is the [[central bank]] of [[Seychelles]]. The Central Bank of Seychelles (CBS), was officially established on 1 January 1983, with the simultaneous dissolution of its precursor, the ''Seychelles Monetary Authority''.<ref name=\"1R\">{{cite web| url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/HistoryOfBank1.html |title=The History of the Central Bank of Seychelles |date=5 April 2020 | access-date=5 April 2020 |publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |\nauthor=Central Bank of Seychelles |location=Victoria, Seychelles}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n\nThe offices of the bank are housed in Central Bank Building, located on Independence Avenue, between the Independence House and the Pirates Arms Building, in [[Victoria, Seychelles| Victoria]], the capital city of Seychelles. The three-storey building is fully air-conditioned and comprises {{convert|3500|m2|0}} of office and storage space.<ref name=\"2R\">{{cite web|publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |title=The Central Bank Building |author=Central Bank of Seychelles | url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/CBSBuilding.html |date=5 April 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020 |location=Victoria}}</ref> The geographical coordinates of the Central Bank Building are:04\u00b037'24.0\"S, 55\u00b027'14.0\"E (Latitude:-4.623333; Longitude:55.453889).<ref name=\"3R\">{{google maps| url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/4%C2%B037'24.0%22S+55%C2%B027'14.0%22E/@-4.6232841,55.4540932,164m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d-4.6233333!4d55.4538889 |title=Location of the Central Bank Building, Victoria, Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn 1974, the Currency Commission of the Seychelles was formed. In 1978, the Seychelles Monetary Authority was established, which in 1983 was transformed into the Central Bank of Seychelles (CBS). Up until 1982, the accounts of the Government of Seychelles were managed by [[Barclays Bank|Barclays Bank International]]. On 29 December 1982 that responsibility was transferred to CBS by passing the \"Central Bank of Seychelles Act 1982\". An amended \"Central Bank of Seychelles Act 2004\" provided for the [[autonomy]] of the bank within the Seychellois government structure.<ref name=\"4R\">{{cite web|title=History Of The Bank | url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/HistoryOfBank.html |date=5 April 2020 |publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020 |author=Central Bank of Seychelles |place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n==Governance==\nThe affairs of the bank are supervised by an eight-person [[board of directors]], chaired by the bank governor. As of April 2020, the following eight individuals comprised the board.<ref name=\"5R\">{{cite web|title=Board Members of Central Bank of Seychelles |url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/BoardMembers.html | publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |date=5 April 2020 | author=Central Bank of Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020 | place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n# Caroline Abel: Governor and [[Chairperson]]\n# Christopher Edmond: First Deputy Governor\n# Jenifer Sullivan: Second Deputy Governor\n# Errol Dias: Director\n# Bertrand Rassool: Director\n# William Otiende Ogara: Director\n# Frank Ally: Attorney General, Director\n# Sherley Marie: Director.\n\n==Governors==\nThe table below illustrates the names of the various Governors of the Central Bank of Seychelles, from its inception, on 1 January 1983.<ref name=\"6R\">{{cite web|newspaper=Seychelles Nation Archives |url=http://www.nation.sc/archive/239928/exhibition-traces-evolution-of-central-banking-in-seychelles |date=28 November 2013 |title=Exhibition traces evolution of central banking in Seychelles |author=[[Seychelles Nation]] |access-date=5 April 2020 |place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin: 0.5em auto\"\n|+ Governors of the Central Bank of Seychelles Since Inception\n! Rank !! Governor !! From !! Until !! Notes\n|-\n| 1 || [[Guy Morel]]  || January 1983 || September 1991 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 2 || Aboo Aumeeruddy || September 1991 || April 1995 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 3 || [[Norman Weber]]  || May 1995 || April 2001 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 4 || Francis Chang-Len]  || May 2001 || October 2008 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 5 || Pierre Laporte  || November 2008 || March 2012 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 6 || [[Caroline Abel]]  || March 2012 || present ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[Central banks and currencies of Africa]]\n*[[Economy of the Seychelles]]\n*[[List of banks in Seychelles]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.cbs.sc/ Central Bank of Seychelles]\n*[https://www.swfinstitute.org/profile/598cdaa50124e9fd2d05abf2 SWFI Profile]\n\n{{Central banks}}\n{{Seychelles topics}}\n\n[[Category:Economy of Seychelles]]\n[[Category:Central banks|Seychelles]]\n[[Category:1983 establishments in Seychelles]]\n[[Category:Banks established in 1983]]\n[[Category:Banks of Seychelles]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Central bank  Seychelles}}\n\n{{Infobox central bank\n| bank_name            = Central Bank of Seychelles\n| bank_name_in_local   = Banque centrale des Seychelles <br />Labank santral Sesel\n| image_1              = Central Bank of Seychelles.jpg\n| image_title_1 \u00a0 \u00a0 \u00a0  = The main office building of Central Bank of Seychelles\n| image_width_1        = \n| image_2              =\n| image_title_2        =\n| image_width_2        =\n| headquarters         = [[Victoria, Seychelles]]\n| coordinates          = {{coord|04|37|24|S|55|27|14|E|display=inline,title}}\n| established          = {{start date and years ago| 1983|01|01|df=y}}\n| ownership            = [[Government of Seychelles]]\n| president            = [[Caroline Abel]]\n| leader_title         = Governor\n| bank_of              = [[Seychelles]]\n| currency             = [[Seychellois rupee]]\n| currency_iso         = SCR\n| logo                 = [[Image:CENTRAL BANK OF SEYCHELLES LOGO.png|thumb|center]]\n| reserves             =\n| reserve_requirements = \n| borrowing_rate       = \n| interest_rate_target = \n| deposit_rate         = \n| IOER                 = \n| website              = {{URL|www.cbs.sc}}\n| preceded             =\n| succeeded            =\n| footnotes            =\n}}\n\nThe '''Central Bank of Seychelles''' ({{lang-fr|Banque centrale des Seychelles}}, [[Seychellois Creole]]: ''Labank santral Sesel''), is the [[central bank]] of [[Seychelles]]. The Central Bank of Seychelles (CBS), was officially established on 1 January 1983, with the simultaneous dissolution of its precursor, the ''Seychelles Monetary Authority''.<ref name=\"1R\">{{cite web| url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/HistoryOfBank1.html |title=The History of the Central Bank of Seychelles |date=5 April 2020 | access-date=5 April 2020 |publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |\nauthor=Central Bank of Seychelles |location=Victoria, Seychelles}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\n\nThe offices of the bank are housed in Central Bank Building, located on Independence Avenue, between the Independence House and the Pirates Arms Building, in [[Victoria, Seychelles| Victoria]], the capital city of Seychelles. The three-storey building is fully air-conditioned and comprises {{convert|3500|m2|0}} of office and storage space.<ref name=\"2R\">{{cite web|publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |title=The Central Bank Building |author=Central Bank of Seychelles | url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/CBSBuilding.html |date=5 April 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020 |location=Victoria}}</ref> The geographical coordinates of the Central Bank Building are:04\u00b037'24.0\"S, 55\u00b027'14.0\"E (Latitude:-4.623333; Longitude:55.453889).<ref name=\"3R\">{{google maps| url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/4%C2%B037'24.0%22S+55%C2%B027'14.0%22E/@-4.6232841,55.4540932,164m/data=!3m1!1e3!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d-4.6233333!4d55.4538889 |title=Location of the Central Bank Building, Victoria, Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIn 1974, the Currency Commission of the Seychelles was formed. In 1978, the Seychelles Monetary Authority was established, which in 1983 was transformed into the Central Bank of Seychelles (CBS). Up until 1982, the accounts of the Government of Seychelles were managed by [[Barclays Bank|Barclays Bank International]]. On 29 December 1982 that responsibility was transferred to CBS by passing the \"Central Bank of Seychelles Act 1982\". An amended \"Central Bank of Seychelles Act 2004\" provided for the [[autonomy]] of the bank within the Seychellois government structure.<ref name=\"4R\">{{cite web|title=History Of The Bank | url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/HistoryOfBank.html |date=5 April 2020 |publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020 |author=Central Bank of Seychelles |place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n==Governance==\nThe affairs of the bank are supervised by an eight-person [[board of directors]], chaired by the bank governor. As of April 2020, the following eight individuals comprised the board.<ref name=\"5R\">{{cite web|title=Board Members of Central Bank of Seychelles |url=https://www.cbs.sc/Aboutus/BoardMembers.html | publisher=Central Bank of Seychelles |date=5 April 2020 | author=Central Bank of Seychelles |access-date=5 April 2020 | place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n# Caroline Abel: Governor and [[Chairperson]]\n# Christopher Edmond: First Deputy Governor\n# Jenifer Sullivan: Second Deputy Governor\n# Errol Dias: Director\n# Bertrand Rassool: Director\n# William Otiende Ogara: Director\n# Frank Ally: Attorney General, Director\n# Sherley Marie: Director.\n\n==Governors==\nThe table below illustrates the names of the various Governors of the Central Bank of Seychelles, from its inception, on 1 January 1983.<ref name=\"6R\">{{cite web|newspaper=Seychelles Nation Archives |url=http://www.nation.sc/archive/239928/exhibition-traces-evolution-of-central-banking-in-seychelles |date=28 November 2013 |title=Exhibition traces evolution of central banking in Seychelles |author=[[Seychelles Nation]] |access-date=5 April 2020 |place=Victoria}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"margin: 0.5em auto\"\n|+ Governors of the Central Bank of Seychelles Since Inception\n! Rank !! Governor !! From !! Until !! Notes\n|-\n| 1 || [[Guy Morel]]  || January 1983 || September 1991 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 2 || Aboo Aumeeruddy || September 1991 || April 1995 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 3 || [[Norman Weber]]  || May 1995 || April 2001 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 4 || Francis Chang-Len]  || May 2001 || October 2008 ||<ref name=\"6R\"/>\n|-\n| 5 || Pierre Laporte  || November