{"title_page": "United Kingdom - European Union Free Trade Agreement", "text_new": "The UK - EU [[Free trade agreement|Free Trade Agreement]] (UK - EU FTA), is a proposed agreement between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and N.Ireland and the European Union that is due to be signed before when the [[Brexit transition period|transitional period ends]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iea.org.uk/the-greenwich-reset-a-future-uk-eu-free-trade-agreement/|title=The Greenwich Reset: A future UK - EU Free Trade Agreement|last=Singham|first=Shanker|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute of Economic Affairs|others=Shanker is an IEA Trade Fellow, having previously been the Director of the International Trade and Competition Unit (ITCU) of the Institute of Economic Affairs. As one of the world\u2019s leading trade and competition lawyers, he has worked on the privatisation of the UK electricity market, the transition of the Soviet, Central and Eastern European economies and the apertura in Latin America. He has worked on the accession of Poland and Hungary to the EU, the WTO accessions of a number of countries, including China and Russia. Shanker was educated at St. Paul\u2019s School, London and has an M.A in Chemistry from Balliol College, Oxford University and postgraduate legal degrees in both the UK and US.|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/uk-europe/opinion/negotiating-a-new-eu-uk-partnership-in-challenging-times/|title=Negotiating a new EU - UK partnership in challenging times|last=McAllister|first=David|date=March 27, 2020|website=Eractiv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+UK - EU Free Trade Agreement[[File:UK_-_EU_Map_.pdf|link=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:UK_-_EU_Map_.pdf|center|thumb|UK = Green and EU = White]]\n|'''Agreement Type'''           Trade Agreement\n|-\n|'''Status'''                            In Negotiation\n|-\n|'''Location (s)'''                   [[London]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Brussels]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa \n|-\n|'''Participants'''                  [[United Kingdom]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[European Union]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n\n(On behalf of 27 [[Member state of the European Union|EU Member States]] \n|-\n|'''Negotiators'''                   [[David Frost (British diplomat)|David Frost]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Michel Barnier]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n|-\n|'''Languages'''                    [[Official languages of the United Nations|All official UK Languages]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Languages of the European Union|All official EU Languages]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n|}\n\n== History ==\n'''Brexit''' \n\nThe UK - EU Free Trade Agreement  negotiations happened as a result of the [[Brexit|United Kingdom\u2019s exit from the European Union or Brexit.]] \n\nThis agreement will signed in addition to the [[Brexit withdrawal agreement|Brexit Withdrawal Agreement]], which was agreed at the conclusion of  [[Brexit negotiations|Brexit Negotiations]].  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2020/02/brexit-isnt-done-guide-eu-uk-trade-negotiations|title=Brexit isn\u2019t done: a guide to the EU-UK trade negotiations|last=Statesman|first=New|date=February 3, 2020|website=New Statesman|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n'''Negotiations''' \n\nThe [[Trade deal negotiation between the UK and EU|UK EU Trade Negotiations]] began on March 31st 2020 and are due to be concluded on the December 31st 2020, after which the treaty will be ratified by both parties and officially enter into force. \n\nThere has currently been one round of trade negotiations which held in person at Brussels, however the second round negotiations have had to be cancelled due to the [[Disease outbreak|outbreak]] of the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/brexit-first-round-trade-talks-eu-confirms-serious-differences-2112045%3f|title=Brexit: First round of trade talks with EU confirms \u2018serious\u2019 differences|last=Gourtsoyannis|first=Paris|date=March 5, 2020|website=The Scotsman|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.co.uk/ft.com/content/0ef6cd0a-6491-11ea-a6cd-df28cc3c6a68|title=Face-to-face Brexit talks cancelled over coronavirus fears|last=(1)Payne /  Brunsden (2)|first=(1) Sebastian / Jim (2)|date=March 12, 2020|website=Financial Times|others=Sebastian Payne is from London and Jim Brunsden is from Brussels|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Draft Legal & Treaty Text   ==\nOn the  20th of March 2020 the  European Union released a full Draft Legal text outlining details of  the UK - EU  Free Trade Agreement they would like to see.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.neweurope.eu/article/eu-uk-exchange-draft-legal-texts-on-future-relationship/|title=EU-UK exchange draft legal texts on future relationship|last=Didili|first=Zoi|date=March 20, 2020|website=New Europe|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> (for document look at the See Also section)\n== Areas Covered in the FTA and Contention Points ==\nThere are many areas covered in the UK free Trade Agreement and  these are:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.export.org.uk/news/487813/Towards-a-Free-Trade-Agreement--the-EUs-initial-negotiating-stance.htm|title=Towards a Free Trade Agreement \u2013 the EU\u2019s initial negotiating stance|last=Mielken|first=Arne|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute for Export and International Trade|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.export.org.uk/news/487863/Towards-a-Free-Trade-Agreement--the-UKs-initial-negotiating-stance.htm|title=Towards a Free Trade Agreement, the UK \u2018s initial negotiating stance|last=Arne|first=Mielken|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute of Exports & International Trade|others=A two-part analysis of the EU and UK negotiating mandates from our Vice President|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n* Economy & Trade  - Trade in Goods  - Trade in Services & Investment \n*- Financial Services \n*- Digital Trade \n*- Capital Market   - Level Playing Field\n*Intellectual Property \n*Public Procurement \n*Environment\n*Security Partnership   - Police Enforcement  \n*- Law Enforcement & Judicial Matters\n*- Foreign Policy, Security & Defence\n*- Thematic  Co - Operation \n*Fisheries\n*Cross Border Transport   \n*- Aviation\n*- Trains  \n*- Buses\n*- Cars \n*- Cross Border Transport of Goods \n*Civil Nuclear \n\n'''Fisheries''' \n\nUnder the EU Trade Proposal the UK and the EU would create and agreement based on the current [[Common Fisheries Policy|Common Fisheries Policy,]] with EU fisherman maintaining free access to UK waters and quotas staying similar to what they were when the uk was a member of the EU.\n\nHowever the UK have rejected this proposal stating that they are taking back control of their fishing waters, and have instead put forward a proposal to have yearly negotiations on access to UK waters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/02/28/fishing-uk-european-union-brexit-trade-talks-cfp/|title=So Long, and Say Thanks for All the Fish|last=Johnson|first=Kieth|date=February 28, 2020|website=Foreign Policy|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n== Documents ==\n[https://ec.europa.eu/info/sites/info/files/200318-draft-agreement-gen.pdf European Union (Draft EU - UK Free Trade Agreement]\n\n== See Also ==\n\n* [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum]]\n* [[Post-Brexit United Kingdom relations with the European Union]]\n\n== Sources ==\n<references />\n", "text_old": "The UK - EU [[Free trade agreement|Free Trade Agreement]] (UK - EU FTA), is a proposed agreement between the United Kingdom of Great Britain and N.Ireland and the European Union that is due to be signed before when the [[Brexit transition period|transitional period ends]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://iea.org.uk/the-greenwich-reset-a-future-uk-eu-free-trade-agreement/|title=The Greenwich Reset: A future UK - EU Free Trade Agreement|last=Singham|first=Shanker|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute of Economic Affairs|others=Shanker is an IEA Trade Fellow, having previously been the Director of the International Trade and Competition Unit (ITCU) of the Institute of Economic Affairs. As one of the world\u2019s leading trade and competition lawyers, he has worked on the privatisation of the UK electricity market, the transition of the Soviet, Central and Eastern European economies and the apertura in Latin America. He has worked on the accession of Poland and Hungary to the EU, the WTO accessions of a number of countries, including China and Russia. Shanker was educated at St. Paul\u2019s School, London and has an M.A in Chemistry from Balliol College, Oxford University and postgraduate legal degrees in both the UK and US.|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/uk-europe/opinion/negotiating-a-new-eu-uk-partnership-in-challenging-times/|title=Negotiating a new EU - UK partnership in challenging times|last=McAllister|first=David|date=March 27, 2020|website=Eractiv|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> \n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+UK - EU Free Trade Agreement[[File:UK_-_EU_Map_.pdf|link=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:UK_-_EU_Map_.pdf|center|thumb|UK = Green and EU = White]]\n|'''Agreement Type'''           Trade Agreement\n|-\n|'''Status'''                            In Negotiation\n|-\n|'''Location (s)'''                   [[London]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Brussels]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa \n|-\n|'''Participants'''                  [[United Kingdom]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[European Union]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n\n(On behalf of 27 [[Member state of the European Union|EU Member States]] \n|-\n|'''Negotiators'''                   [[David Frost (British diplomat)|David Frost]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Michel Barnier]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n|-\n|'''Languages'''                    [[Official languages of the United Nations|All official UK Languages]] \ud83c\uddec\ud83c\udde7\n[[Languages of the European Union|All official EU Languages]] \ud83c\uddea\ud83c\uddfa\n|}\n\n== History ==\n'''Brexit''' \n\nThe UK - EU Free Trade Agreement  negotiations happened as a result of the [[Brexit|United Kingdom\u2019s exit from the European Union or Brexit.]] \n\nThis agreement will signed in addition to the [[Brexit withdrawal agreement|Brexit Withdrawal Agreement]], which was agreed at the conclusion of  [[Brexit negotiations|Brexit Negotiations]].  <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2020/02/brexit-isnt-done-guide-eu-uk-trade-negotiations|title=Brexit isn\u2019t done: a guide to the EU-UK trade negotiations|last=Statesman|first=New|date=February 3, 2020|website=New Statesman|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n'''Negotiations''' \n\nThe [[Trade deal negotiation between the UK and EU|UK EU Trade Negotiations]] began on March 31st 2020 and are due to be concluded on the December 31st 2020, after which the treaty will be ratified by both parties and officially enter into force. \n\nThere has currently been one round of trade negotiations which held in person at Brussels, however the second round negotiations have had to be cancelled due to the [[Disease outbreak|outbreak]] of the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/brexit-first-round-trade-talks-eu-confirms-serious-differences-2112045%3f|title=Brexit: First round of trade talks with EU confirms \u2018serious\u2019 differences|last=Gourtsoyannis|first=Paris|date=March 5, 2020|website=The Scotsman|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.google.co.uk/ft.com/content/0ef6cd0a-6491-11ea-a6cd-df28cc3c6a68|title=Face-to-face Brexit talks cancelled over coronavirus fears|last=(1)Payne /  Brunsden (2)|first=(1) Sebastian / Jim (2)|date=March 12, 2020|website=Financial Times|others=Sebastian Payne is from London and Jim Brunsden is from Brussels|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Draft Legal & Treaty Text   ==\nOn the  20th of March 2020 the  European Union released a full Draft Legal text outlining details of  the UK - EU  Free Trade Agreement they would like to see.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.neweurope.eu/article/eu-uk-exchange-draft-legal-texts-on-future-relationship/|title=EU-UK exchange draft legal texts on future relationship|last=Didili|first=Zoi|date=March 20, 2020|website=New Europe|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> (for document look at the See Also section)\n== Areas Covered in the FTA and Contention Points ==\nThere are many areas covered in the UK free Trade Agreement and these are:<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.export.org.uk/news/487813/Towards-a-Free-Trade-Agreement--the-EUs-initial-negotiating-stance.htm|title=Towards a Free Trade Agreement \u2013 the EU\u2019s initial negotiating stance|last=Mielken|first=Arne|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute for Export and International Trade|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.export.org.uk/news/487863/Towards-a-Free-Trade-Agreement--the-UKs-initial-negotiating-stance.htm|title=Towards a Free Trade Agreement, the UK \u2018s initial negotiating stance|last=Arne|first=Mielken|date=February 4, 2020|website=Institute of Exports & International Trade|others=A two-part analysis of the EU and UK negotiating mandates from our Vice President|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n* Trade\n* Fisheries\n* Security co - operation\n* Aviation<br />\n\n'''Fisheries''' \n\nUnder the EU Trade Proposal the UK and the EU would create and agreement based on the current [[Common Fisheries Policy|Common Fisheries Policy,]] with EU fisherman maintaining free access to UK waters and quotas staying similar to what they were when the uk was a member of the EU.\n\nHowever the UK have rejected this proposal stating that they are taking back control of their fishing waters, and have instead put forward a proposal to have yearly negotiations on access to UK waters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/02/28/fishing-uk-european-union-brexit-trade-talks-cfp/|title=So Long, and Say Thanks for All the Fish|last=Johnson|first=Kieth|date=February 28, 2020|website=Foreign Policy|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n== Documents ==\n[https://ec.europa.eu/info/sites/info/files/200318-draft-agreement-gen.pdf European Union (Draft EU - UK Free Trade Agreement]\n\n== See Also ==\n\n* [[2016 United Kingdom European Union membership referendum]]\n* [[Post-Brexit United Kingdom relations with the European Union]]\n\n== Sources ==\n<references />\n", "name_user": "ChefBear01", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added info", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom_-_European_Union_Free_Trade_Agreement"}
{"title_page": "Saurabh Mittal", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Advert|date=March 2020}}\n{{Undisclosed paid|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = January 2020}}{{Infobox person\n| name               = Saurabh Mittal\n| image              = Saurabhmittal.jpg\n| birth_date         = {{Birth year and age|1973}}\n| birth_place        = [[India]]\n| nationality        = [[India]]\n| education          = [[Harvard Business School]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Indian Institute of Technology]]\n| occupation         = Founder and Chairman of Mission Holdings\nChairman of Incedo Inc.\nVice Chairman of [[ONE Championship]]\n}}\n\n'''Saurabh Mittal''' is a [[Singapore]]-based Indian [[Businessperson|businessman]], [[entrepreneur]], [[investor]], and [[Philanthropy|philanthropist]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/indiabulls-co-founder-emerges-among-richest-singaporeans-13159|title=Indiabulls co-founder emerges among richest Singaporeans|date=2017-07-28|website=International Business Times, Singapore Edition|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/spores-50-richest-people-became-11-richer-in-total|title=Singapore's 50 richest became 11% richer in past year: Forbes|last=hermes|date=2017-07-28|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> He is the Founder and [[Chairman]] of Mission Holdings,<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.missionholdings.com/|title=Mission Holdings is an investment firm led by entrepreneur Mr. Saurabh Mittal|website=www.missionholdings.com|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> a private investment holding company.\n\n== Education ==\n\nMittal attended the [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|Indian Institute of Technology]] in [[Delhi]] for a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in [[Electrical engineering|Electrical Engineering]], where he was the Best Graduating Student.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/distinguished-alumni-awards-2017-3|title=Distinguished Alumni Awards 2017 {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Mittal also holds an [[MBA]] from [[Harvard Business School]] and graduated as a [[Baker Scholar]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\n== Career ==\n\nIn 1999, Mittal co-founded [[Indiabulls]],<ref name=\":0\" /> a financial services and real estate conglomerate in India, with his undergraduate classmates from the Indian Institute of Technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yosuccess.com/success-stories/sameer-gehlaut-indiabulls/|title=Sameer Gehlaut|date=2015-12-01|website=Yo! Success|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> He served as [[Vice-Chairman|Vice Chairman]] of its [[Board of directors|Board of Directors]] until he stepped down in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kalesh|first=Baiju|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/indiabulls-partners-sameer-gehlaut-saurabh-mittal-and-rajiv-rattan-to-divide-operations/articleshow/38103495.cms|title=Indiabulls partners Sameer Gehlaut, Saurabh Mittal and Rajiv Rattan to divide operations|date=2014-07-10|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-19|last2=Babar|first2=Kailash}}</ref> \n\nHe later joined [[Farallon Capital]] as an investment associate in 2001 before he became a full partner at Noonday Capital, an affiliate of Farallon, in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportspromedia.com/movers-and-shakers/one-championship-saurabh-mittal|title=ONE Championship appoints Saurabh Mittal as vice chairman|website=www.sportspromedia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Mittal left both Farallon and Noonday in 2011.{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n\nWhile studying for his [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] at [[Harvard Business School]], Mittal befriended [[Chatri Sityodtong]], and the pair later established martial arts promotion ONE Championship in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/from-duelling-classmates-to-business-partners|title=From duelling classmates to business partners|last=hermes|date=2017-11-06|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/magazines/wealth-december-2017/kicking-off-a-storm|title=Kicking off a storm|last=Cua|first=Genevieve|date=2017-12-05|website=The Business Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> Mittal was appointed Vice Chairman of the company in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onefc.com/press-releases/saurabh-mittal-joins-one-championship-as-vice-chairman/|title=Saurabh Mittal Joins ONE Championship As Vice Chairman {{!}} ONE Championship - Press Releases|date=2018-03-13|website=ONE Championship - The Home Of Martial Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onefc.com/senior-leadership/|title=Senior Leadership|website=ONE Championship - The Home Of Martial Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> \n\nIn 2011, Mittal founded Incedo Inc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.incedoinc.com/leader/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Incedo \u2013 Tech Solutions, Consulting, Data, Analytics, Digital Transformation|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> with operating partners to focus on data and [[analytics]] in the US.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.incedoinc.com/leader/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Incedo \u2013 Tech Solutions, Consulting, Data, Analytics, Digital Transformation|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In 2017, Nitin Seth took over from Mittal as [[Chief executive officer|Chief Executive Officer]] of Incedo,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Peermohamed|first=Alnoor|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/former-flipkart-executive-nitin-seth-joins-incedo-as-ceo-117102300724_1.html|title=Former Flipkart executive Nitin Seth joins Incedo as CEO|date=2017-10-23|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/hr-leadership/leadership/flipkarts-nitin-seth-joins-tech-services-company-incedo-as-ceo/articleshow/61195064.cms|title=Flipkart's Nitin Seth joins tech services company Incedo as CEO|date=2017-10-24|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> while Mittal remained as Chairman. \n\nIn 2014, Mittal set up Mission Holdings,<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.asiatatler.com/people/saurabh-mittal|title=Saurabh Mittal|last=Singapore|first=Tatler|date=2017-10-16|website=Tatler Singapore|language=en-SG|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> a private investment holding company with a focus on financial services,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fintechfutures.com/2019/11/goldman-sachs-leads-50m-series-c-funding-round-for-credit-card-platform-deserve/|title=Goldman Sachs leads $50m Series C funding round for credit card platform Deserve|last=November 2019|first=7th|website=FinTech Futures|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> media, real estate, and technology, and he is its Chairman and sole shareholder.\n\nIn 2019, Mittal was ranked as the 44th richest person in Singapore with a net worth of $700 million.<ref>https://www.forbes.com/profile/saurabh-mittal/#38cd0d386791</ref>\n\n== Board memberships ==\n\n* Chairman, Mission Holdings\n* Chairman, Incedo Inc.\n* Vice Chairman, [[ONE Championship]]\n\n== Philanthropy ==\n\nMittal has served on Harvard Business School\u2019s Advisory Board, is a Founder and Trustee of Plaksha University,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plaksha.org/aboutus|title=Plaksha University|website=plaksha.org|language=en-us|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> and is a Founder and Board Member of the IIT Delhi Endowment Fund.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/president-india-launches-endowment-fund-iit-delhi|title=President of India launches Endowment Fund of IIT Delhi {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> He is also member of the governing body of Parivaar, a [[charitable organization]] focused on the care and development of highly-vulnerable children,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parivaar.org/about/governing-bodyboard-of-directors/|title=Governing Body {{!}} Parivaar|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> and a member of the Founder\u2019s Circle of Avasara Academy, a school dedicated to developing young Indian women.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://avasara.in/govAndAdv|title=Founder's Circle|website=avasara.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> In 2020, Mittal donated RS. 10 Crore towards building the Mittal Sports Centre at IIT Delhi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/mr-saurabh-mittal-iit-delhi-alumnus-donates-rs-10-crore-sports-complex?page=3|title=Mr. Saurabh Mittal, IIT Delhi Alumnus, donates Rs. 10 Crore for Sports Complex {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMittal has three children.<ref>https://sg.asiatatler.com/society/saurabh-mittal-and-chatri-sityodtong</ref>\n\n== Honors ==\nDistinguished Alumnus Award 2017, [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/48th-convocation-iit-delhi-3|title=48th Convocation at IIT Delhi {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/in/news-releases/iit-delhi-honors-saurabh-mittal-chairman-of-incedo-and-mission-holdings-with-the-2017-distinguished-alumnus-award-656031493.html|title=I.I.T Delhi Honors Saurabh Mittal, Chairman of Incedo and Mission Holdings, With the 2017 Distinguished Alumnus Award|last=Limited|first=Incedo Technology Solutions|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Chatri Sityodtong]]\n* [[ONE Championship]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Indian expatriates in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Indian Institute of Technology Delhi alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard Business School alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Advert|date=March 2020}}\n{{Undisclosed paid|date=March 2020}}\n}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date = January 2020}}{{Infobox person\n| name               = Saurabh Mittal\n| image              = Saurabhmittal.jpg\n| birth_date         = {{Birth year and age|1973}}\n| birth_place        = [[India]]\n| nationality        = [[India]]\n| education          = [[Harvard Business School]]\n| alma_mater         = [[Indian Institute of Technology]]\n| occupation         = Founder and Chairman of Mission Holdings\nChairman of Incedo Inc.\nVice Chairman of [[ONE Championship]]\n}}\n\n'''Saurabh Mittal''' is a [[Singapore]]-based Indian [[Businessperson|businessman]], [[entrepreneur]], [[investor]], and [[Philanthropy|philanthropist]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.sg/indiabulls-co-founder-emerges-among-richest-singaporeans-13159|title=Indiabulls co-founder emerges among richest Singaporeans|date=2017-07-28|website=International Business Times, Singapore Edition|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/spores-50-richest-people-became-11-richer-in-total|title=Singapore's 50 richest became 11% richer in past year: Forbes|last=hermes|date=2017-07-28|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> He is the Founder and [[Chairman]] of Mission Holdings,<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.missionholdings.com/|title=Mission Holdings is an investment firm led by entrepreneur Mr. Saurabh Mittal|website=www.missionholdings.com|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> a private investment holding company.\n\n== Education ==\n\nMittal attended the [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|Indian Institute of Technology]] in [[Delhi]] for a [[Bachelor of Science|BS]] in [[Electrical engineering|Electrical Engineering]], where he was the Best Graduating Student.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/distinguished-alumni-awards-2017-3|title=Distinguished Alumni Awards 2017 {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Mittal also holds an [[MBA]] from [[Harvard Business School]] and graduated as a [[Baker Scholar]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Forbes|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> \n\n== Career ==\n\nIn 1999, Mittal co-founded [[Indiabulls]],<ref name=\":0\" /> a financial services and real estate conglomerate in India, with his undergraduate classmates from the Indian Institute of Technology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yosuccess.com/success-stories/sameer-gehlaut-indiabulls/|title=Sameer Gehlaut|date=2015-12-01|website=Yo! Success|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> He served as [[Vice-Chairman|Vice Chairman]] of its [[Board of directors|Board of Directors]] until he stepped down in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kalesh|first=Baiju|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/banking/finance/indiabulls-partners-sameer-gehlaut-saurabh-mittal-and-rajiv-rattan-to-divide-operations/articleshow/38103495.cms|title=Indiabulls partners Sameer Gehlaut, Saurabh Mittal and Rajiv Rattan to divide operations|date=2014-07-10|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-19|last2=Babar|first2=Kailash}}</ref> \n\nHe later joined [[Farallon Capital]] as an investment associate in 2001 before he became a full partner at Noonday Capital, an affiliate of Farallon, in 2005.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportspromedia.com/movers-and-shakers/one-championship-saurabh-mittal|title=ONE Championship appoints Saurabh Mittal as vice chairman|website=www.sportspromedia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> Mittal left both Farallon and Noonday in 2011.{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n\nWhile studying for his [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] at [[Harvard Business School]], Mittal befriended [[Chatri Sityodtong]], and the pair later established martial arts promotion ONE Championship in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/business/from-duelling-classmates-to-business-partners|title=From duelling classmates to business partners|last=hermes|date=2017-11-06|website=The Straits Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businesstimes.com.sg/magazines/wealth-december-2017/kicking-off-a-storm|title=Kicking off a storm|last=Cua|first=Genevieve|date=2017-12-05|website=The Business Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> Mittal was appointed Vice Chairman of the company in 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onefc.com/press-releases/saurabh-mittal-joins-one-championship-as-vice-chairman/|title=Saurabh Mittal Joins ONE Championship As Vice Chairman {{!}} ONE Championship - Press Releases|date=2018-03-13|website=ONE Championship - The Home Of Martial Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.onefc.com/senior-leadership/|title=Senior Leadership|website=ONE Championship - The Home Of Martial Arts|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> \n\nIn 2011, Mittal founded Incedo Inc.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.incedoinc.com/leader/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Incedo \u2013 Tech Solutions, Consulting, Data, Analytics, Digital Transformation|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> with operating partners to focus on data and [[analytics]] in the US.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.incedoinc.com/leader/saurabh-mittal/|title=Saurabh Mittal|website=Incedo \u2013 Tech Solutions, Consulting, Data, Analytics, Digital Transformation|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> In 2017, Nitin Seth took over from Mittal as [[Chief executive officer|Chief Executive Officer]] of Incedo,<ref>{{Cite news|last=Peermohamed|first=Alnoor|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/companies/former-flipkart-executive-nitin-seth-joins-incedo-as-ceo-117102300724_1.html|title=Former Flipkart executive Nitin Seth joins Incedo as CEO|date=2017-10-23|work=Business Standard India|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/hr-leadership/leadership/flipkarts-nitin-seth-joins-tech-services-company-incedo-as-ceo/articleshow/61195064.cms|title=Flipkart's Nitin Seth joins tech services company Incedo as CEO|date=2017-10-24|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> while Mittal remained as Chairman. \n\nIn 2014, Mittal set up Mission Holdings,<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sg.asiatatler.com/people/saurabh-mittal|title=Saurabh Mittal|last=Singapore|first=Tatler|date=2017-10-16|website=Tatler Singapore|language=en-SG|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> a private investment holding company with a focus on financial services,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fintechfutures.com/2019/11/goldman-sachs-leads-50m-series-c-funding-round-for-credit-card-platform-deserve/|title=Goldman Sachs leads $50m Series C funding round for credit card platform Deserve|last=November 2019|first=7th|website=FinTech Futures|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> media, real estate, and technology, and he is its Chairman and sole shareholder.\n\n== Board memberships ==\n\n* Chairman, Mission Holdings\n* Chairman, Incedo Inc.\n* Vice Chairman, [[ONE Championship]]\n\n== Philanthropy ==\n\nMittal has served on Harvard Business School\u2019s Advisory Board, is a Founder and Trustee of Plaksha University,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://plaksha.org/aboutus|title=Plaksha University|website=plaksha.org|language=en-us|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> and is a Founder and Board Member of the IIT Delhi Endowment Fund.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/president-india-launches-endowment-fund-iit-delhi|title=President of India launches Endowment Fund of IIT Delhi {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-19}}</ref> He is also member of the governing body of Parivaar, a [[charitable organization]] focused on the care and development of highly-vulnerable children,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://parivaar.org/about/governing-bodyboard-of-directors/|title=Governing Body {{!}} Parivaar|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref> and a member of the Founder\u2019s Circle of Avasara Academy, a school dedicated to developing young Indian women.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://avasara.in/govAndAdv|title=Founder's Circle|website=avasara.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref> In 2020, Mittal donated RS. 10 Crore towards building the Mittal Sports Centre at IIT Delhi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/mr-saurabh-mittal-iit-delhi-alumnus-donates-rs-10-crore-sports-complex?page=3|title=Mr. Saurabh Mittal, IIT Delhi Alumnus, donates Rs. 10 Crore for Sports Complex {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nMittal has three children.<ref>https://sg.asiatatler.com/society/saurabh-mittal-and-chatri-sityodtong</ref>\n\n== Honors ==\nDistinguished Alumnus Award 2017, [[Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|Indian Institute of Technology, Delhi]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iitd.ac.in/content/48th-convocation-iit-delhi-3|title=48th Convocation at IIT Delhi {{!}} Indian Institute of Technology Delhi|website=www.iitd.ac.in|access-date=2020-03-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prnewswire.com/in/news-releases/iit-delhi-honors-saurabh-mittal-chairman-of-incedo-and-mission-holdings-with-the-2017-distinguished-alumnus-award-656031493.html|title=I.I.T Delhi Honors Saurabh Mittal, Chairman of Incedo and Mission Holdings, With the 2017 Distinguished Alumnus Award|last=Limited|first=Incedo Technology Solutions|website=www.prnewswire.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Chatri Sityodtong]]\n* [[ONE Championship]]\n\n== Ref