{"title_page": "2013 Ball Hockey World Championship", "text_new": "{{cleanup|date=December 2014|reason=The tables are covering the whole axis of the page.}}\n{{Infobox international hockey competition\n| tourney_name = Ball Hockey World Championship\n| year = 2013\n| other_titles =\n| image = \n| size = \n| caption =\n| country = Canada\n| dates = 2 \u2013 6 June 2013\n| num_teams = 17\n| venues = 1\n| cities = 1\n| winners_other = \n| count = \n| second_other = \n| third_other = \n| games = 17\n| goals = 194\n| attendance = \n| scoring_leader = {{flagicon|CZE}} [[Jan Bacovsk\u00fd]]\n| points = \n| prevseason = [[2011 Ball Hockey World Championship|2011]]\n| nextseason = [[2015 Ball Hockey World Championship|2015]]\n}}\n\nThe '''2013 [[Ball Hockey World Championship]]''' was the tenth ball hockey world championship held by ISBHF in [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St.John's]], Canada.  [[Slovakia men's national ball hockey team|Slovakia]] won their second title. [[Canada men's national ball hockey team|Canada]] captured the bronze medal with a 7 \u2013 3 victory over the [[Portugal men's national ball hockey team|Portugal]]. The [[Canada women's national ball hockey team]] captured the gold medal in women's play, avenging the silver medal from 2011. \n\n== Group A ==\n\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n|show_positions=n\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=CAN|name_CAN={{flagicon|CAN}} [[Canada men's national ball hockey team|Canada]]\n|team2=SVK|name_SVK={{flagicon|SVK}} [[Slovakia men's national ball hockey team|Slovakia]]\n|team3=GRE|name_GRE={{flagicon|GRE}} [[Greece men's national ball hockey team|Greece]]\n|team4=GER|name_GER={{flagicon|GER}} [[Germany men's national ball hockey team|Germany]]\n|team5=PAK|name_PAK={{flagicon|PAK}} [[Pakistan men's national ball hockey team|Pakistan]]\n|win_CAN=4|draw_CAN=0|loss_CAN=0|gf_CAN=25|ga_CAN=5\n|win_SVK=3|draw_SVK=0|loss_SVK=1|gf_SVK=16|ga_SVK=5\n|win_GRE=2|draw_GRE=0|loss_GRE=2|gf_GRE=12|ga_GRE=5\