onship]]''' was the tenth ball hockey world championship held by ISBHF in [[St. John's, Newfoundland and Labrador|St.John's]], Canada.  [[Slovakia men's national ball hockey team|Slovakia]] won their second title. [[Canada men's national ball hockey team|Canada]] captured the bronze medal with a 7 \u2013 3 victory over the [[Portugal men's national ball hockey team|Portugal]]. The [[Canada women's national ball hockey team]] captured the gold medal in women's play, avenging the silver medal from 2011. \n\n== Group A ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=\"175\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|Pld|Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|W|Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|D|Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|L|Lost}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|GF|Goals for}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|GA|Goals against}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|GD|Goal difference}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{abbr|Pts|Points}}\n|- bgcolor=\"#ccffcc\"\n|align=left|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Canada men's national ball hockey team|Canada]]\n|4||4||0||0||25||5||+20||'''8'''\n|- bgcolor=\"#9BDDFF\"\n|align=left|{{flagicon|SVK}} [[Slovakia men's national ball hockey team|Slovakia]]\n|4||3||0||1||16||5||+11||'''6'''\n|- bgcolor=\"#9BDDFF\"\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GRE}} [[Greece men's national ball hockey team|Greece]]\n|4||2||0||2||12||5||+7||'''4'''\n|- bgcolor=\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Germany men's national ball hockey team|Germany]]\n|4||1||0||3||8||26||&minus;18||'''2'''\n|- bgcolor=\n|align=left|{{flagicon|PAK}} [[Pakistan men's national ball hockey team|Pakistan]]\n|4||0||0||4||8||28||&minus;20||'''0'''\n|}\n\n{{Ice hockey box\n| bg = #eeeeee\n| date = \n| time = \n| team1 = [[Slovakia men's national ball hockey team|Slovakia]] {{flagicon|SVK}}\n| score = 8 \u2013 1\n| team2 = {{flagicon|PAK}} [[Pakistan men's national ball hockey team|Pakistan]]\n| progression = 1\u20130<br/>1\u20131<br/>2\u20131<br/>3\u20131<br/>4\u20131<br/>5\u20131<br/>6\u20131<br/>7\u20131<br/>8\u20131 \n| periods = (2\u20131, 2\u20130, 4\u20130)